  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "The Treasury of David",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "54 And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "55 He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "56 Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "57 But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers' they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "58 For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "59 When God heard this, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred Israel:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "60 So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "among men;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "61 And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy's hand.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "62 He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "63 The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "64 Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "65 Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "66 And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he put them to a perpetual reproach.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "continued...",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
